https://dev.azure.com/azure-sdk/internal/_build/results?buildId=6043417&amp;view=logs&amp;j=cb756bb2-5a44-589d-a17a-a4d39d58f7d8&amp;t=f596852c-a8ec-58bf-0df1-493482eaa7dd            ","state":"OPEN","user":{"login":"JoshLove-msft"},"labels":["Client","CodeGen"],"created_at":"2026-03-21T04:47:19Z","updated_at":"2026-03-21T04:48:06Z"},{"number":57316,"title":"HealthcareApis test recordings need re-recording (stale EventHub serialization)","body":"## Problem

HealthcareApis recorded tests fail with `TestRecordingMismatchException` when run with `UseProjectReferenceToAzureClients=true` (used in Azure.Core PR CI batches).

**Error:** `.properties: Missing in record JSON` - the EventHub namespace PUT request body now includes `&#34;properties&#34;: {}` but the recordings don&#39;t have it.

## Root Cause

- HealthcareApis recordings were updated in PR #46491 (Oct 11, 2024)
- EventHubs SDK got WriteCore serialization update in PR #46169 (Oct 15, 2024) - 4 days AFTER the recordings
- The WriteCore change made EventHub serialization write `&#34;properties&#34;` unconditionally
- Normally this doesn&#39;t surface because HealthcareApis tests use EventHubs from NuGet (1.2.1, pre-WriteCore)
- With `UseProjectReferenceToAzureClients=true`, local EventHubs source (1.3.0-beta.2, post-WriteCore) is used instead, causing the mismatch

## Impact

Affects any Azure.Core PR that randomly gets HealthcareApis in its `UseProjectReferenceToAzureClients=true` integration batch.

## Fix Required

Re-record HealthcareApis tests to capture the updated EventHub serialization format.

Found during #57200.
